1.title: Linda Robson & Daniel Galmiche

episode of.title: Saturday Morning with James Martin (TV Series 2017– )

1.plot: James Martin presents the brand new morning magazine show featuring plenty of hearty food. His guests today are Birds of a Feather star Linda Robson and chef Daniel Galmiche.

2.title: Gareth Malone & Brian Turner

episode of.title: Saturday Morning with James Martin (TV Series 2017– )

2.plot: James Martin presents the morning magazine show. His guests are choirmaster Gareth Malone and chef Brian Turner. Recipes include chicken escalope and strawberry and cream cake.

3.title: Martine McCutcheon & Paul Ainsworth

episode of.title: Saturday Morning with James Martin (TV Series 2017– )

3.plot: James Martin hosts the cookery show, with guests Martine McCutcheon and Paul Ainsworth. Highlights on the menu include crab and prawn cocktail and lamb shoulder with peas.

4.title: Carol Kirkwood & Nathan Outlaw

episode of.title: Saturday Morning with James Martin (TV Series 2017– )

4.plot: James Martin is joined by broadcaster Carol Kirkwood and chef Nathan Outlaw. He also attempts to make lemon meringue pie while being driven by Jason Plato.

5.title: Belinda Carlisle & Michael Caines

episode of.title: Saturday Morning with James Martin (TV Series 2017– )

5.plot: James Martin is joined by singer Belinda Carlisle and chef Michael Caines, and today's menu includes pizza Margherita, chocolate souffle and BBQ baby back ribs.

6.title: Camilla Dallerup & Paul Rankin

episode of.title: Saturday Morning with James Martin (TV Series 2017– )

6.plot: James Martin is joined by his old Strictly Come Dancing partner Camilla Dallerup and chef Paul Rankin. Today's menu includes southern fried chicken and crab cakes.

7.title: Judy Murray & Jun Tanaka

episode of.title: Saturday Morning with James Martin (TV Series 2017– )

7.plot: James Martin is at home for another Saturday morning filled with fantastic food, fast cars, and entertainment. James is joined by tennis coach Judy Murray and chef Jun Tanaka.

8.title: Gok Wan & Claude Bosi

episode of.title: Saturday Morning with James Martin (TV Series 2017– )

8.plot: James Martin welcomes Gok Wan and chef Claude Bosi to his home. Today's menu includes fish pie, steamed sponge and custard, and Malaysian lobster.

9.title: Amy Childs & Sat Bains

episode of.title: Saturday Morning with James Martin (TV Series 2017– )

9.plot: James martin welcomes Amy Childs and Sat Bains. On the menu are Singapore crab, pheasant Kiev, and sea bass. James has another spin with Jason Plato in the Ariel Nomad racing car.

10.title: Alison Steadman & Galton Blackiston

episode of.title: Saturday Morning with James Martin (TV Series 2017– )

10.plot: James Martin welcomes Alison Steadman and Galton Blackiston for another morning of good food and entertainment. Today's menu includes T-bone plaice with champagne sauce.

11.title: Jack Savoretti & Daniel Galmiche

episode of.title: Saturday Morning with James Martin (TV Series 2017– )

11.plot: James Martin presents a mix of cookery and chat. He is joined be musician Jack Savoretti and chef Daniel Galmiche, while dished include sea bass baked in salt and seasonal rabbit.

12.title: Shane Richie, Tony Tobin & Kenny Atkinson

episode of.title: Saturday Morning with James Martin (TV Series 2017– )

12.plot: James Martin welcomes Shane Richie and chefs Tony Tobin and Kenny Atkinson to his home for another morning of good food and entertainment.

13.title: Cheryl Baker, Jay Aston & Michael Caines

episode of.title: Saturday Morning with James Martin (TV Series 2017– )

13.plot: James Martin welcomes singers Cheryl Baker and Jay Aston and chef Michael Caines to his home for another morning of good food and entertainment.

14.title: Alexander Armstrong & Nick Nairn

episode of.title: Saturday Morning with James Martin (TV Series 2017– )

14.plot: James martin welcomes Pointless host Alexander Armstrong and chef Nick Nairn to his home for another morning of good food and entertainment.

15.title: At Christmas - Harry Judd & Rachel Allen

episode of.title: Saturday Morning with James Martin (TV Series 2017– )

15.plot: The host welcomes musician Harry Judd and chef Rachel Allen to his home, with beef wellington, gravadlax and brandy snaps on the menu.

16.title: At Christmas - Adam Woodyatt & Paul Rankin

episode of.title: Saturday Morning with James Martin (TV Series 2017– )

16.plot: Eastenders star Adam Woodyatt and chef Paul Rankin join James for steak with wild mushrooms and red wine sauce, cardamom, and pistachio buns.

17.title: At Christmas - Galton Blackiston & Lisa Allen

episode of.title: Saturday Morning with James Martin (TV Series 2017– )

17.plot: James Martin is joined by Galton Blackiston and Lisa Allen for Christmas turkey, lobster pasta, and clementine and almond cake.

18.title: At Christmas - Jimi Mistry, Flavia Cacace & Brian Turner

episode of.title: Saturday Morning with James Martin (TV Series 2017– )

18.plot: Chef Brian Turner, Jimi Mistry and Flavia Cacace join James for slow-cooked lamb shoulder and a prune, apple and Christmas pudding crumble.

19.title: Galton Blackiston, Amanda Lamb & Jonathan Phang

episode of.title: Saturday Morning with James Martin (TV Series 2017– )

19.plot: James Martin is joined by chef Galton Blackiston and guests Amanda Lamb and Jonathan Phang for chicken chasseur, jerk pork and chocolate mousse cake.

20.title: Nigel Howarth & Jo Wood

episode of.title: Saturday Morning with James Martin (TV Series 2017– )

20.plot: James Martin is joined by chef Nigel Howarth and guest Jo Wood for devilled potted shrimps, duck confit and pheasant schnitzel.

21.title: Chris Tarrant & Aggi Sverrisson

episode of.title: Saturday Morning with James Martin (TV Series 2017– )

21.plot: Chris Tarrant and chef Aggi Sverrisson join James Martin at home. On the menu today are beef stew and dumplings and jam roly poly with custard.

22.title: Milton Jones & Jun Tanaka

episode of.title: Saturday Morning with James Martin (TV Series 2017– )

22.plot: Comedian Milton Jones and chef Jun Tanaka join James Martin at home for a menu including deep-fried chilli beef and French onion soup.

23.title: Kate Garraway & Lisa Allen
